Content: think about what the market cap of the dow or nasdaq would be if government didnt threaten to steal what people don't contribute to their 401k's...  Government basically says, "I am going to steal X% of your income.  But if you commit to putting some of your income into this walled garden of government-manipulated assets, we will steal less of that portion."  Of course money is going to get shoved into that area.  People aren't buying stocks because they believe in the companies they are investing in.  They buy stocks so less of their money gets jacked by .gov.  Imagine the market cap of any of the indices if government wasn't pointing guns at peoples' heads telling them where to push their money.
